\n| coordinates         = {{coord|46|39|N|11|9|E|type:city(2,268)_region:IT|display=inline,title}}\n| coordinates_footnotes = \n| region              = [[Trentino-Alto Adige/S\u00fcdtirol]]\n| province            = [[South Tyrol]] (BZ)\n| frazioni            = \n| mayor_party         = \n| mayor               = Walter Mairhofer\n| area_footnotes      = \n| area_total_km2      = 12.8\n| population_footnotes = \n| population_total    = 2,710\n| population_as_of    = Nov. 2017\n| pop_density_footnotes = \n| population_demonym  = German: Marlinger<br>Italian: marlinghesi\n| elevation_footnotes = \n| elevation_m         = \n| twin1               = \n| twin1_country       = \n| saint               = \n| day                 = \n| postal_code         = 39020\n| area_code           = 0473\n| website             = {{official website|http://www.gemeinde.marling.bz.it/}}\n| footnotes           = \n}}\n'''Marling''' ({{IPA-de|\u02c8marl\u026a\u014b}}; {{lang-it|Marlengo}}  {{IPA-it|mar\u02c8le\u014b\u0261o|}}) is a ''[[comune]]'' (municipality) in [[South Tyrol]] in northern [[Italy]], located about {{convert|25|km|mi}} northwest of [[Bolzano]].\n\n== Geography ==\nAs of the year 2017, it had a population of 2,710 and an area of {{convert|12.8|km2|mi2}}.<ref name=\"istat\">All demographics and other statistics: Italian statistical institute [[National Institute of Statistics (Italy)|Istat]].</ref>\n\nMarling borders the following municipalities: [[Tscherms]], [[Algund]], [[Lana, South Tyrol|Lana]], [[Merano]] and [[Partschins]].\n\n==History==\n\n===Coat-of-arms===\nThe shield is [[argent]] a [[fess]] [[Azure (heraldry)|azure]] and a [[gules]] [[lion (heraldry)|rampant lion]] . These are the arms of the Lords of ''Marling'' who lived in two castles in the village until 1426. The emblem was adopted in 1966.\n<ref>[http://www.ngw.nl/int/ita/m/marling.htm Heraldry of the World: Marling]</ref>\n\n[[File:Marlengo-1908.jpg|thumb|A view of Marling towards Meran from a 1908 postcard]]\n\n==Society==\n\n===Linguistic distribution===\nAccording to the 2011 census, 86.41% of the population speak [[German language|German]], 13.41% Italian and 0.17% [[Ladin language|Ladin]] as first language.<ref>{{cite journal |date=June 2012 |title=Volksz\u00e4hlung 2011/Censimento della popolazione 2011 |journal=astat info |issue=38 |pages=6\u20137 |publisher=Provincial Statistics Institute of the Autonomous Province of South Tyrol|url=http://www.provinz.bz.it/astat/de/service/256.asp?news_action=300&news_image_id=563169 |accessdate=2012-06-14 }}</ref>\n\n===Demographic evolution===\n<timeline>\nColors=\n id:lightgrey value:gray(0.9)\n id:darkgrey value:gray(0.8)\n id:sfondo value:rgb(1,1,1)\n id:barra value:rgb(0.6,0.7,0.8)\n\nImageSize = width:455 height:303\nPlotArea = left:50 bottom:50 top:30 right:30\nDateFormat = x.y\nPeriod = from:0 till:3000\nTimeAxis = orientation:vertical\nAlignBars = justify\nScaleMajor = gridcolor:darkgrey increment:1000 start:0\nScaleMinor = gridcolor:lightgrey increment:200 start:0\nBackgroundColors = canvas:sfondo\n\nBarData=\n bar:1861 text:1861\n bar:1871 text:1871\n bar:1881 text:1881\n bar:1901 text:1901\n bar:1911 text:1911\n bar:1921 text:1921\n bar:1931 text:1931\n bar:1936 text:1936\n bar:1951 text:1951\n bar:1961 text:1961\n bar:1971 text:1971\n bar:1981 text:1981\n bar:1991 text:1991\n bar:2001 text:2001\n\nPlotData=\n color:barra width:20 align:left\n\n bar:1861 from: 0 till:0\n bar:1871 from: 0 till:0\n bar:1881 from: 0 till:0\n bar:1901 from: 0 till:0\n bar:1911 from: 0 till:0\n bar:1921 from: 0 till:1427\n bar:1931 from: 0 till:1935\n bar:1936 from: 0 till:2085\n bar:1951 from: 0 till:1930\n bar:1961 from: 0 till:1743\n bar:1971 from: 0 till:1867\n bar:1981 from: 0 till:2013\n bar:1991 from: 0 till:2041\n bar:2001 from: 0 till:2197\n\nPlotData=\n\n bar:1861 at:0 fontsize:XS text: ? shift:(-8,5)\n bar:1871 at:0 fontsize:XS text: ? shift:(-8,5)\n bar:1881 at:0 fontsize:XS text: ? shift:(-8,5)\n bar:1901 at:0 fontsize:XS te