1&sr=8-2&keywords=florence+and+the+machine+spectrum |title=Florence + the Machine - Spectrum (Say My Name) |date=10 July 2012 |accessdate=20 August 2012}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Universal Republic]]\n|-\n| 7 May 2013<ref name=\"Pop/CHR\">{{cite web |url=http://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases}}</ref>\n| [[Contemporary hit radio|Mainstream]] Airplay\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of number-one dance singles of 2012 (U.S.)]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|3}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{YouTube|iC-_lVzdiFE|''Spectrum'' Music Video}}\n* {{MetroLyrics song|florence-and-the-machine|spectrum-say-my-name}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{Florence and the Machine}}\n{{Calvin Harris}}\n\n[[Category:2012 singles]]\n[[Category:Florence and the Machine songs]]\n[[Category:Irish Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Island Records singles]]\n[[Category:Music videos directed by David LaChapelle]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Scotland]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Paul Epworth]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Paul Epworth]]\n[[Category:UK Singles Chart number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Florence Welch]]\n[[Category:Billboard Dance Club Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:2011 songs]]\n[[Category:Synth-pop songs]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2012 song by Florence and the Machine}}\n{{refimprove|date=August 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2013}}\n{{Use British English|date=January 2013}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Spectrum (Say My Name)\n| cover      = Florence and the Machine - Spectrum.png\n| alt        = Single cover\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Florence and the Machine]]\n| album      = [[Ceremonials]]\n| released   = {{Start date|2012|7|6|df=yes}}\n| format     = {{hlist|[[12-inch single|12\"]]|[[Music download|digital download]]}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Baroque pop]]|[[art pop]]|[[indie pop]] <small> (album version)</small><br />\n|[[orchestral pop]]|[[contemporary R&B|R&B]]|[[krautrock]]|[[disco]] <small>(single version)</small>}}\n| length     = {{unbulleted list|{{Duration|m=5|s=11}} {{small|(album version)}}|{{Duration|m=3|s=38}} {{small|(remix version)}}}}\n| label      = [[Island Records|Island]]\n| writer     = {{hlist|[[Florence Welch]]|[[Paul Epworth]]}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|Paul Epworth|[[Calvin Harris]] {{small|(remix)}}}}\n| prev_title = [[Breath of Life (Florence and the Machine song)|Breath of Life]]\n| prev_year  = 2012\n| next_title = [[Lover to Lover]]\n| next_year  = 2012\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|id=iC-_lVzdiFE|title=\"Spectrum\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Spectrum'''\" is a song by English [[indie rock]] band [[Florence and the Machine]] from their second studio album ''[[Ceremonials]]'' (2011). It was written by lead singer [[Florence Welch]] and [[Paul Epworth]] with production being handled by Epworth. The band premiered the song during a concert at Brooklyn's Creators Project on 15 October 2011, prior to the release of the album. The album version of \"Spectrum\" is a downtempo [[orchestral pop]], [[contemporary R&B|R&B]], [[krautrock]] and [[disco]] song. The accompanying [[music video]] for the song premiered on 30 May 2012. It was directed by [[David LaChapelle]] and [[Johnny Byrne (choreographer)|John Byrne]].\n\nA remix of the album version of \"Spectrum\", titled \"'''Spectrum (Say My Name)'''\", was released on 6 July 2012 by Island Records, serving as the fourth single from Ceremonials. Scottish DJ [[Calvin Harris]] remixed \"Spectrum\", producing the uptempo single. \"Spectrum (Say My Name)\" became the group's first single to peak at number one on the UK Singles Chart, selling 64,816 copies in its first week. It also reached number one in Ireland and Scotland and has peaked within the top five in Australia and New Zealand.\n\n==Background and composition==\nFlorence and the Machine premiered \"Spectrum\" along with two other songs from the album, \"[[Never Let Me Go (Florence and the Machine song)|Never Let Me Go]]\" and \"Heartlines\", as part of their [[set list]] at [[Brooklyn]]'s Creators Project on 15 October 2011, two weeks before the release of the album.<ref>Sources talking about the premiere of \"Spectrum\", \"Never Let Me Go\" and \"Heartlines\" on 15 October 2011 during the band's [[set list]] at New York's Creators Project before the release of ''Ceremonials'':\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/news/florence-and-the-machine/59836|title=Watch Florence And The Machine perform three new tracks from 'Ceremonials' - video|work=[[NME]]|publisher=[[IPC Media]]|date=16 October 2011|accessdate=2 July 2012}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/news/a345974/florence--the-machine-perform-three-new-tracks-live-video.html|title=Florence + the Machine perform three new tracks live - video|publisher=[[Digital Spy]]. [[Hachette Filipacchi M\u00e9dias]]|first=Robert|last=Copsey|date=17 October 2011|accessdate=2 July 2012}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2011/10/watch-florence-the-machine-debut-3-new-songs-at-cr.html|title=Watch Florence and the Machine Debut Three New Songs at Creator's Project|work=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]|publisher=[[Wolfgang's Vault]]|first=K.|last=Alexander Smith|date=17 October 2011|accessdate=2 July 2012}}\n*{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2011/10/18/showbiz/creators-project-art-music-tech/|title=Creators Project brings together art, music and tech|publisher=[[CNN]]|first=Abbey|last=Goodman|date=18 October 2011|accessdate=2 July 2012}}\n</ref> Musically, \"Spectrum\" is a downtempo [[orchestral pop]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://diymag.com/archive/florence-and-the-machine-ceremonials |title=Florence & The Machine - Ceremonials |publisher=DIY magazine |accessdate=5 May 2016}}</ref> [[contemporary R&B|R&B]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nme.com/reviews/florence-and-the-machine/12419 |title=Album review: Florence + The Machine - 'Ceremonials' |publisher=NME |accessdate=4 May 2016}}</ref> [[krautrock]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/album-florence-the-machine-ceremonials-island-2376712.html |title=Album: Florence + the Machine, Ceremonials (Island) |newspaper=The Independent |accessdate=4 May 2016}}</ref> and [[disco]] song with [[Drum kit|drums]] while backing vocals repeatedly sing \"Say my name\" throughout the choruses. According to the sheet music published by [[Universal Music Publishing Group]] on the website Musicnotes.com, the song is set in the key [[B minor]].<ref name=\"musicnotes\">{{cite web|title=Spectrum - Sheet Music (Digital Download)|first1=Florence|last1=Welch|first2=Paul|last2=Epworth|publisher=Musicnotes.com. [[Universal Music Publishing Group]]}}</ref> The song's beat is set in [[Time signature|common time]], and moves at a [[tempo]] of 124 beats per minute.<ref name=\"musicnotes\"/> Welch's vocals span from the note of F#3 to the note of F#5 or B5 in the [[Calvin Harris]] remix.<ref name=\"musicnotes\"/>\n\n==Critical reception==\n\"Spectrum\" received mostly positive reviews by critics. While reviewing ''Ceremonials'', Jillian Mapes of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' complimented Welch's vocal performance, stating, \"'Say my name,' she howls then later croons, both filled with sensuality. Welch's impressive vocal range and volume are firing on all cylinders here.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Mapes |first=Jillian |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/465357/florence-the-machine-ceremonials-track-by-track-review |title=Florence + The Machine, 'Ceremonials': Track-By-Track Review |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |date=2 November 2011 |accessdate=28 June 2012}}</ref> A writer of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' praised the song calling it \"a huge, churchy tune, even in the context of the band's typically bombastic blend of [[arena rock]] and [[gospel music|gospel]].\"<ref name=\"rollstone\"/> Lewis Corner from [[Digital Spy]] gave the song four stars out of five, saying \"if there's one thing latest single 'Spectrum' proves, it's that she knows how to write a distinctive uptempo number without compromising her style.\"<ref name=\"digitalspy\"/> He added that the song \"[...] belts over a rapturous chorus complete with rousing piano and delicate strings - demonstrating that techno synths are not the only key to a euphoric hook.\"<ref name=\"digitalspy\">{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/singlesreviews/a391975/florence--the-machine-spectrum-single-review.html|title=Florence + the Machine: \"Spectrum\" - Single review - Music Singles Review|first=Lewis|last=Corner|publisher=[[Digital Spy]]. [[Hachette Filipacchi M\u00e9dias]]|date= 6 July 2012|accessdate=6 July 2012}}</ref>\n\nMatthew Cole from ''[[Slant Magazine]]'' said along with \"Lover to Lover\" and \"Remain Nameless\"; \"spectacular when taken alone or on a playlist.\"<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/florence-and-the-machine-ceremonials/2666|title=Florence and the Machine - Ceremonials|magazine=[[Slant Magazine]]|first=Matthew|last=Cole|date=30 October 2011|accessdate=15 September 2012}}</ref> Kitty Empire from ''[[The Guardian]]'' gave it a mixed remark, saying \"Clubby and kaleidoscopic, 'Spectrum' sounds like another rallying cry.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2011/oct/30/florence-machine-ceremonials-review |title=Florence and the Machine: Ceremonials \u2013 review|work=[[The Observer]]|publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]]|first=Kitty|last=Empire|date=30 October 2011|accessdate=15 September 2012}}</ref> Margaret Wappler of ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' said they could hear a \"harp gorgeously flutter[s] and dips around her.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/music_blog/2011/10/album-review-florence-the-machines-ceremonials.html|title=Album review: Florence + the Machine's 'Ceremonials'|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|publisher=[[Tribune Company]]|date=31 October 2011|first=Margaret|last=Wappler|accessdate=15 September 2012}}</ref> Chris Saunders from [[musicOMH]] compared it, musically, to the song from Florence's previous record ''[[Lungs (album)|Lungs]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.musicomh.com/albums/florence-and-the-machine-2_1011.htm|title=Florence And The Machine - Ceremonials (Island)|publisher=[[musicOMH]]|first=Chris|last=Saunders|date=31 October 2011|accessdate=15 September 2012}}</ref> ''[[The Independent]]'' commented; \"The only time she and The Machine stray from the formula is the Krautrock-disco motorik of 'Spectrum'; elsewhere, declamatory piano chords and burring organ underpin the banked [...]\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/album-florence--the-machine-ceremonials-island-2376712.html|title=Album: Florence + the Machine, Ceremonials (Island )|work=[[The Independent]]|publisher=Independent Print Limited|first=Andy|last=Gill|date=28 October 2011|accessdate=15 September 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\n\n===Background===\nAn accompanying music video for the song was released on Florence and the Machine's [[YouTube]] account on 30 May 2012. Directed by [[David LaChapelle]] and [[Johnny Byrne (choreographer)|John Byrne]], the video depicts ballet dancers of California's Southland Ballet Academy/Festival Ballet Theatre pirouetting, jumping, and dancing around Welch. During an interview, Welch spoke about her collaboration with LaChapelle, \"It was a complete dream to work with David LaChapelle. I collected his books as a teenager, and I fantasised that he would direct the video for 'Spectrum' from the moment the song was written. I still can't believe it actually happened, and I'm completely overjoyed that he felt such a connection with the song.\"<ref name=\"clash\">{{cite web |last=Murray |first=Robin |url=http://www.clashmusic.com/news/watch-florence-the-machine-spectrum |title=Watch: Florence & The Machine \u2013 Spectrum |work=[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]] |date=30 May 2012 |accessdate=2 July 2012}}</ref> During an interview, LaChapelle also spoke about his collaboration with Welch, \"It's a beautiful song that really touched me and inspired me to create imagery that matches its power. 'Spectrum' is free of scepticism, irony, and the coldness one finds in a lot of contemporary popular music. It's the opposite\u2014full of light, positivity and authentic joy. I hope that I can do justice to this moving modern classic.\"<ref name=\"clash\"/>\n\n===Reception===\nUpon the release of the video, critics praised Welch's look and the video's dark atmosphere. A writer of ''Rolling Stone'' wrote, \"Music video legend David LaChappelle rose to the challenge of making a clip for the song, matching its drama and energy with a vivid color pallette and incredibly theatrical staging.\"<ref name=\"rollstone\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/videos/florence-and-the-machines-ultra-theatrical-spectrum-clip-20120530 |title=Florence and the Machine's Ultra-Theatrical 'Spectrum (Say My Name)' Clip |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |publisher=[[Jann Wenner|Wenner Media]] |date=30 May 2012 |accessdate=28 June 2012}}</ref> Robbie Daw of [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] stated the video's visual is \"as bombastic and over the top as the song itself [...] there's enough completely koo koo eye candy being hurled at us that we're barely even paying attention to the song itself.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Daw |first=Robbie |url=http://idolator.com/6547762/florence-the-machine-spectrum-video |title=Florence + The Machine's \"Spectrum (Say My Name)\" Video: Watch |publisher=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]. [[Buzz Media]] |date=30 May 2012 |accessdate=28 June 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Live performances==\nThe band performed the song on [[The X Factor (U.S. season 1)#Week 8: Semi-final (December 14/15)|first series]] of the [[The X Factor (U.S.)|American version of ''The X Factor'']] during its semi-finals.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=563IavLCjAA</ref> Florence and the Machine added the song to the [[set list]] of their second worldwide [[Ceremonials Tour]] (2011\u201312) where the song was performed during the encore of the concerts along with \"[[No Light, No Light]]\".{{citation needed|date=August 2014}} On 12 September 2012, Florence performed a stripped-down version of the song on ''[[Late Night with Jimmy Fallon]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.latenightwithjimmyfallon.com/blogs/2012/09/florence-the-machine-perform-spectrum-say-my-name/ |title=Florence + The Machine Perform \"Spectrum (Say My Name)\" |publisher=NBCUniversal Media|accessdate=13 September 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Calvin Harris remix==\nA remix of the album version of \"Spectrum\", titled \"'''Spectrum (Say My Name)'''\", was released on 6 July 2012 by [[Island Records]], serving as the fourth single from ''Ceremonials''. Scottish DJ [[Calvin Harris]] remixed \"Spectrum\", producing the uptempo [[electro house]]-inspired single.<ref name=\"digitalspy\" /> \"Spectrum (Say My Name)\" received positive reviews from music critics, praising the production and Welch's vocals.<ref name=\"digitalspy\" /> Commercially, it became the group's first single to peak at number one on the [[UK Singles Chart]], selling 64,816 copies in its first week. It also reached number one in Ireland and Scotland and has peaked within the top five in Australia and New Zealand.\n\n===Background and development===\nOn 25 May 2012, a lyric video was released for the [[Calvin Harris]] remix. The song was released as the album's fifth single on 5 July 2012.<ref name=\"itunes\"/> It was serviced to radio in the UK on 2 July 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.radio1.gr/music/forthcoming_uk_singles.htm |title=New Releases U.K. \u2013 Forthcoming Singles |publisher=Radio1 Rodos Greece |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/67bCUOYln |archivedate=12 May 2012 |accessdate=3 July 2012}}</ref> On the release of the single, the Calvin Harris remix was released. Lewis Corner of Digital Spy commented that \"While the single version is near perfection, an accompanying Calvin Harris remix highlights just how big a Florence house anthem can be\".<ref name=\"digitalspy\" /> The instrumental version of \"Spectrum\" was used extensively during the [[BBC]]'s coverage of the [[2012 Summer Olympics|London 2012 Olympic Games]], often as the backing track to their round-up of the day's sporting action.{{citation needed|date=August 2014}}\n\n===Commercial performance===\n\"Spectrum\" debuted at number 104 on the [[UK Singles Chart]] based on the sales of the album version.<ref>{{cite web |last=Williams |first=Paul |url=http://www.musicweek.com/story.asp?storycode=1050348 |title=Midweek Charts: Florence eyeing first singles chart-topper |work=[[Music Week]] |publisher=Intent Media |date=11 July 2012 |accessdate=13 July 2012}}</ref> On 15 July 2012, following the release of the Calvin Harris remix of the song, it climbed the chart to become the band's first number-one single in the UK, selling 64,816 copies in its first week.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.musicweek.com/story.asp?storycode=1050399 |title=Official Charts Analysis: Newton Faulkner needs just 16k sales to hit No.1 |work=Music Week |publisher=Intent Media |date=16 July 2012 |accessdate=16 July 2012}}</ref> The song stayed on top of the chart for three weeks. It also debuted at number 35 on the [[New Zealand Singles Chart]], until rising to number two, becoming the group's first top ten single in that country. It peaked at the top spot in the Republic of Ireland. In the UK, it was the best-selling single of the third quarter of 2012, selling 453,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-biggest-selling-singles-of-the-summer-revealed-1626/|title=The biggest selling singles of the summer revealed! |date=4 October 2012 |accessdate=4 October 2012}}</ref> The song has sold 554,000 copies in the UK in 2012, and was the 19th best-selling single of 2012.<ref name=\"chartuk\">{{cite web |url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/the-official-top-40-biggest-selling-singles-of-2012-revealed-1784/ |title=The Official Top 40 Biggest Selling Singles Of 2012 revealed! |author=Dan Lane |publisher=Official Charts Company |date=2 January 2013|accessdate=5 January 2013}}</ref> However, in 2013, it was certified platinum for selling over 600,000 copies. It is Florence + the Machine's best-selling single in the United Kingdom.\n\n==Track listing==\n{{track listing\n| headline  = \"Spectrum (Say My Name)\" Remixes [[Extended play|EP]]<ref name=\"itunes\">{{cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/gb/album/spectrum-say-my-name-remixes/id531158564 |title=Spectrum (Say My Name) <nowiki>[Remixes]</nowiki> \u2013 EP by Florence + The Machine |publisher=[[iTunes Store]] (UK). [[Apple Inc.|Apple Inc]] |accessdate=28 June 2012}}</ref>\n| title1    = Spectrum (Say My Name)\n| note1     = [[Calvin Harris]] Remix\n| length1   = 3:38\n| title2    = Spectrum (Say My Name)\n| note2     = [[AlunaGeorge]] Remix\n| length2   = 3:29\n| title3    = Spectrum (Say My Name)\n| note3     = [[Maya Jane Coles]] Remix\n| length3   = 5:00\n| title4    = Spectrum (Say My Name)\n| note4     = Taito Tikaro and Flavio Zarza Remix\n| length4   = 7:26\n}}\n\n==Charts and certifications==\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2012-13)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Australia|4|artist=Florence + The Machine|song=Spectrum (Say My Name)|rowheader=true|accessdate=23 July 2012}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"{{singlechart|Austria|51|artist=Florence + The Machine|song=Spectrum (Say My Name)}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|2|artist=Florence + The Machine|song=Spectrum (Say My Name)|rowheader=true|accessdate=20 July 2012}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia|9|artist=Florence + The Machine|song=Spectrum (Say My Name)|row